<paragraph id="A10836F4FFF11D5936E4FA7C2163F0FA" blockId="38.[213,350,1437,1461]" box="[213,350,1437,1461]" pageId="38" pageNumber="1439">
<emphasis id="93C3EAE6FFF11D5936E4FA7C2163F0FA" box="[213,350,1437,1461]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="1439">Morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A10836F4FFF11D5936E4FA252324F314" blockId="38.[213,1170,1476,1628]" pageId="38" pageNumber="1439">
As in original description. In addition: fore wing subbasal cell scleromes without setae ventrally; vein m-cu 2.8 times length of 2-SR+M, forming an angle of 110 
<superScript id="56C29BBCFFF11D59321FFA01240AF0BE" attach="left" box="[1070,1079,1504,1521]" fontSize="7" pageId="38" pageNumber="1439">◦</superScript>
with 3- CU1; vein 2-SR strongly bent medially; vein 2-M 2.5 times length of r-m. Hind wing basal cell posteriorly and subbasal cell largely glabrous; discal+subdiscal cell with small area of reduced setosity adjacent to vein cu-a.
</paragraph>
